---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Writing â€” Efe Ertugrul">
	<main>
		<header>
			<h1>Writing</h1>
			<p class="intro">
				Short, opinionated pieces about infrastructure, research systems, and what actually happens when you ship.
			</p>
		</header>

		<section class="posts">
			<article class="post">
				<h2>Why Research Code Collapses in Production</h2>
				<p class="date">Coming soon</p>
				<p>
					Notebooks and scripts work until you need reliability, scale, or someone else to run them. What breaks, why it breaks, and what changes when you're accountable for uptime.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="post">
				<h2>Metadata is Infrastructure</h2>
				<p class="date">Coming soon</p>
				<p>
					Everyone treats metadata as an afterthought until queries fail, pipelines break, or compliance audits happen. Why metadata design is an engineering problem, not a documentation problem.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="post">
				<h2>Kubernetes is Not Your Bottleneck</h2>
				<p class="date">Coming soon</p>
				<p>
					Most performance problems aren't in your orchestration layer. They're in your queries, your data model, or your API design. When K8s actually matters and when it's a distraction.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="post">
				<h2>What Shipping ML Systems Actually Costs</h2>
				<p class="date">Coming soon</p>
				<p>
					Training a model is 10% of the work. The other 90% is data pipelines, versioning, monitoring, retraining workflows, and making sure it doesn't fail silently. Real numbers from production systems.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="post">
				<h2>Schema Translation: The Unsexy Work That Unblocks Everything</h2>
				<p class="date">Coming soon</p>
				<p>
					How converting XSD to LinkML enabled cross-platform validation for bioimaging metadata. The engineering decisions, the tradeoffs, and why this work matters more than it sounds like it does.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
	}

	header {
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.intro {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: #4b5563;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.posts {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3rem;
	}

	.post {
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.post:last-of-type {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: #111827;
	}

	.date {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: #6b7280;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.post p:last-of-type {
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: #374151;
		margin: 0;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		main {
			padding: 3rem 1.25rem;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: 2rem;
		}

		.posts {
			gap: 2.5rem;
		}
	}
</style>

